{"lemma":"سُرُجِ","slug":"سُرُجِ","root":"س.ر.ج","root_slug":"س-ر-ج","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ر-ج","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سِراج","root":"سرج","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19484","n19488"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%8F%D8%AC%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lamp, luminary, lantern"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"used as a part of plant-names"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"saddler"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Aramaic שְׁרָגָא (šerāgā) (in Classical Syriac ܫܪܳܓܳܐ), from Parthian *𐫢𐫡𐫀𐫄 (*šrʾɣ /⁠širāɣ⁠/).\n\nBorrowed from Aramaic סַרָּגָא (sarrāgā) (in Classical Syriac ܣܰܪܳܓܳܐ), from סְרַג (srag, “to bind, to plait”) (in Classical Syriac ܣܪܰܓ)."},"ipa":["/si.raːd͡ʒ/","/sar.raːd͡ʒ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19484","headword_ar":"سَرَجَ","root":"srj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarojN","text_ar":"سَرْجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TK,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He lied;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarija","text_ar":"سَرِجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) but the latter is outweighed [in authority]; (TA;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadaja","text_ar":"سَدَجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O:) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sr~j","text_ar":"سرّج","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araja","text_ar":"شَرَجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O and K * in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$rj","text_ar":"شرج"},{"kind":"text","text":".) You say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"takal~ama fulaAnN bikalimapK fasaraja EalayohaA biA^usoruwjapK","text_ar":"تَكَلَّمَ فُلَانٌ بِكَلِمَةٍ فَسَرَجَ عَلَيْهَا بِاُسْرُوجَةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one spoke a word,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sentence, and followed it with a lie"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraja Alka*iba","text_ar":"سَرَجَ الكَذِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarojN","text_ar":"سَرْجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He forged the lie."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also 2.]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarajN","text_ar":"سَرَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as an inf. n., signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being bright,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shining."},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL.) ―         -b2-  [And hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarija","text_ar":"سَرِجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarajN","text_ar":"سَرَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TK,) said of one's face, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, beautiful:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O:) or, said of a man, (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, beautiful in his face:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) but said by some, to be post-classical; and by some, to be strange. (TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarajato $aEorahaA","text_ar":"سَرَجَتْ شَعْرَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K, TA, but not in the CK,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sr~jt","text_ar":"سرّجت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA, but not in the O,) [thought by SM to be a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sr~Ht","text_ar":"سرّحت"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the unpointed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H","text_ar":"ح"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a woman, O)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plaited her hair;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sajaratohu","text_ar":"سَجَرَتْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O.)       -A4-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraja","text_ar":"سَرَجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", expl. as signifying “"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ephippio instruxit instravitve"},{"kind":"text","text":"equum ” by Golius and Freytag, by the latter as on the authority of the S and K, I do not find in either of those lexicons, nor in any other. The verb having this meaning is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Asrj","text_ar":"اسرج"},{"kind":"text","text":"only.]"}],"source_refs":["O","K","TK","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n19488","headword_ar":"سَرْجٌ","root":"srj","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain appertenance"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse or similar beast, (Msb, K, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb;) i. e., his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHol","text_ar":"رَحْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saddle"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) an Arabic word; or, accord. to the Shifá el-Ghaleel, arabicized from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"srk","text_ar":"سرك"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is written by Freytag"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$rk","text_ar":"شرك"},{"kind":"text","text":", and said by him to be Pers., but I know not either of these two words in Pers. with an apposite meaning]: (TA:) dim. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"surayojN","text_ar":"سُرَيْجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) and pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suruwjN","text_ar":"سُرُوجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh, Msb, TA.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAla","text_ar":"مَالَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarojuka","text_ar":"سَرْجُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thy affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case, was"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has become, in a disordered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an unsound, state:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a proverbial saying. (Ham p. 242.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}